<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  Mesmer LLC ("Company," "We," "Us," or "Our"), doing business as SimClient AI ("DBA SimClient AI"),
  respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it through this Privacy Policy.
</p>

<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  This Privacy Policy governs access to and use of our websites and mobile applications, including
  Mesmer: AI Hypnosis &amp; Sleep and SimClientAI (collectively, the "Services" or "Apps"), as well
  as any content, functionality, and services offered, whether as a guest or registered user. The
  policy applies to information collected on the Services, and through email, text, or other
  electronic messages between you and Mesmer LLC.
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">Age Restrictions</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  The Services are not intended for persons under 18 years of age. The Company does not knowingly
  collect personal information from minors and will delete such information if discovered. Users
  under 18 should not provide information, register, or access the Services.
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">Information We Collect Through Our Mobile Apps</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  When you use our mobile Apps, we and our third-party service providers collect the following data
  to operate the Apps, manage your account, process subscriptions, and understand how the Apps are
  used:
</p>
<ul class="mb-6 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-body text-cream-200 marker:text-cream-300">
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Account information.</strong> If you create an account
    or sign in using email and password, Google Sign-In, or Sign in with Apple, we collect your email
    address, display name, and profile photo (where provided by you or the sign-in provider), and a
    unique user identifier. You may also use the Apps anonymously with a temporary account identifier.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Content you provide.</strong> We collect information
    you enter into the Apps, such as the goals, feelings, or topics you provide to generate a
    personalized session. This content is stored to deliver and improve your sessions.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Device and analytics identifiers.</strong> We collect
    device and analytics identifiers used to associate app usage with your account and device for
    analytics purposes.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">App activity.</strong> We collect information about how
    you interact with the Apps, such as sessions started and completed, features used, and content
    accessed, for analytics purposes.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Purchase history.</strong> When you subscribe or make a
    purchase, we collect records of your transactions and subscription status to deliver and manage
    your subscription.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Push notification tokens.</strong> If you enable
    notifications, we collect a device push token so we can notify you (for example, when a custom
    session is ready).
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Apple Health (optional, iOS only).</strong> If you
    enable the Apple Health integration, the Apps write your completed mindfulness minutes to Apple
    Health on your device. We do not read data from Apple Health, and this information is stored on
    your device by Apple, not transmitted to us.
  </li>
</ul>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  This data is transmitted off your device to us and to the third-party service providers described
  below, except where noted (such as Apple Health data, which remains on your device).
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">Third-Party Service Providers in Our Apps</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  We use the following third-party services to operate our Apps. These providers process certain data
  on our behalf and in accordance with their own privacy practices:
</p>
<ul class="mb-6 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-body text-cream-200 marker:text-cream-300">
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Google Firebase</strong> &mdash; provides
    authentication, database, storage, and backend functions. Firebase processes account information,
    user identifiers, and content you provide.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">RevenueCat</strong> &mdash; processes subscription and
    purchase history data to manage in-app subscriptions.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Mixpanel</strong> &mdash; processes device identifiers
    and app activity data to provide usage analytics.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Google Sign-In and Sign in with Apple</strong> &mdash;
    used to authenticate you if you choose those sign-in methods; they provide us your email, name, and
    profile photo as permitted by you.
  </li>
</ul>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  Payments for subscriptions are processed by the applicable app store (Apple App Store or Google
  Play), subject to their respective privacy policies.
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">Information Collection (Website)</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  The Company collects information both voluntarily provided and automatically gathered on our Website.
</p>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Voluntarily Provided Information.</strong> Users provide
  information through forms, contact submissions, surveys, search queries, comments, feedback, or
  product/service orders. This information supports delivery of requested services, performance
  improvement, and promotional communications.
</p>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Automatic Data Collection (Website).</strong> The Website
  employs automatic data collection technologies, such as Google Analytics, to collect information
  about your equipment, browsing actions, and patterns. This includes location data, traffic patterns,
  communications data, computer type, internet connection, IP address, operating system, and browser
  type.
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  Our Website uses standard technologies called "cookies" and server logs to collect information about
  site usage. A cookie is a small text file, often containing an anonymous unique identifier, stored on
  your device.
</p>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  The Company reserves the right to use technological equivalents of cookies, including social media
  pixels, to tailor advertising messages on social media platforms.
</p>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  <strong class="font-medium text-cream-100">Third-Party Tracking:</strong> Third-party providers may
  use cookies, web beacons, or tracking technologies to collect information about online activities for
  interest-based advertising, which the Company does not control.
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">Email Communications</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  The Company retains email content, addresses, and responses with the same security protections as
  other communications. The Company commits to keeping email addresses confidential and will not
  disclose them except as outlined in the disclosure section.
</p>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  The Company maintains compliance with the CAN-SPAM Act. All emails include sender identification,
  contact information, and unsubscribe instructions. Users may opt out by clicking unsubscribe links or
  contacting
  <a
    href="mailto:info@mesmer.life"
    class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-light"
  >info@mesmer.life</a>.
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">How We Use Information</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  Information is used to provide and operate the Services, authenticate users and manage accounts,
  generate and deliver personalized sessions, process and manage subscriptions, send notifications you
  have enabled, measure and improve performance through analytics, provide offers, fulfill contracts,
  administer customer service, and display tailored advertisements based on user characteristics and
  interests.
</p>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  The Company may share information with third parties for commission-based product/service offerings
  if users opt in.
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">How We Share Information</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  The Company does not sell or rent your personal information. We share information as follows:
</p>
<ul class="mb-6 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-body text-cream-200 marker:text-cream-300">
  <li>
    With third-party service providers that process data on our behalf to operate the Apps and
    Services, including Google Firebase (authentication, database, backend), RevenueCat (subscription
    management), and Mixpanel (analytics), and website analytics providers.
  </li>
  <li>With subsidiaries, affiliates, or service providers.</li>
  <li>With third parties enforcing our Terms of Use or agreements.</li>
  <li>With successors during business transitions.</li>
  <li>
    With entities legally compelled by law or government, or when the Company believes in good faith
    that disclosure is necessary to protect legal rights.
  </li>
</ul>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  We retain your data for as long as necessary to provide the Services and as required for legal, tax,
  accounting, or fraud-prevention purposes. You may delete your account and associated data at any time
  directly within the App's Profile menu, which removes your account information, saved content,
  generated sessions, and activity. Instructions are also available at
  <a
    href="https://mesmer.life/delete-account"
    class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-light"
  >https://mesmer.life/delete-account</a>.
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">Security Measures</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  The Company uses commercially reasonable methods to secure information you provide and data we collect
  automatically, including standard security protocols and reputable third-party vendors. Data
  transmitted between our Apps and our service providers is encrypted in transit using industry-standard
  protocols.
</p>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  Email is noted as insecure; sensitive information like credit card details is transmitted via Secure
  Sockets Layer (SSL) and never via email.
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">Policy Updates</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  Changes are posted on the policy page. Material changes are communicated via email and website
  notices. Users are responsible for maintaining current contact information and reviewing updates.
</p>

<h2 class="mb-4 mt-12 text-xl font-medium text-cream-100">GDPR Rights (European Union Users)</h2>
<p class="mb-6 text-body text-cream-200">
  EU residents have rights including: access, rectification, or erasure of their data; restriction of or
  objection to processing; data portability; withdrawal of consent without affecting prior lawful
  processing; and the right to file a complaint with a supervisory authority. The Company collects only
  necessary information for contracts and does not mandate consent for unnecessary processing.
</p>

